#579
A Dimly Lit House~
You have entered a spacious, one room house.  Thick curtains have been
pulled across all the windows, letting in only thin streams of light.
Bookcases line most of the wall space, tables and workbenches occupy
much of the floor.  An unmade bed sits in the northwest corner near
a large, blackened-stone fireplace.  Burning candles have been set
randomly on whatever surface hasn't been cluttered with books and
papers and alchemy equipment.
~
