#925
A Shadowy Hideout~
A narrow ladder attached to the east wall leads down into this damp
room. It is approximately thirty feet square and made of stone,
obviously not by a skilled craftsman.  The air is musty and their are
only a few candles to light the room, casting flickering shadows.
Stores of provisions and weapons, as well as other equipment needed
for outdoor survival are stacked along the southern wall.  A large
group of men, some dressed in armor, sit with their backs to the
walls discussing in hushed tones.
~
