Your attention is immediately drawn to the south.  A giant archway, made
of polished black stone, provides passage through the town's outer wall.
This is the intersection of Mammon Ave, which leads north, and Azazel
Street, which leads east and west.  Ornamental trees and other bushes line
the town wall, following the southern side of Azazel Street.  A metal plaque
has been attached to the keystone of the archway.
