#7176
Outside the North Gate of New Genesia~
A large clearing before the North Gate of the city.  The city walls extend
to the east and west.  An enormous archway made of polished black stone
provides entrance into the town.  A golden plaque is mounted on the
keystone of the archway.  Dense forest surrounds you to the north, east
and west.  There is a trail leading north through the trees. and there is
enough room between the forest and the town walls to walk east and west.
~
