#7177
Outside the Towne Walls~
You are walking through the underbrush surrounding the walls of New
Genesia. The town's wall is to the south, only a few feet away.  It
is constructed entirely from huge blocks of granite, fitted together
almost seamlessly.  Upon closer inspection of the wall, you can see
jagged pieces of glass protruding from the seams.  This would deter
almost any thief from attempting to scale these walls.  To the north
lies dense forested grounds.
